  <p>Earthy notes of truffle and dried herbs echo the mushroom flavors while bright acidity cuts through the cream.</p>
  
  <h3>Louis Jadot Chassagne-Montrachet ($65)</h3>
  <p>Rich, buttery Chardonnay with enough weight to match the risotto's creaminess and subtle oak notes.</p>
  
  <h3>G.D. Vajra Barbera d'Alba ($22)</h3>
  <p>Fresh acidity and soft tannins with earthy cherry notes that complement mushroom umami perfectly.</p>
  
  <h3>Domaine Huet Vouvray Sec ($35)</h3>
  <p>Crisp Chenin Blanc with honeyed notes and zippy acidity to balance the rich, creamy risotto.</p>

  <p>Remember, the best pairing is ultimately the wine you enjoy. These recommendations provide a starting point for your own delicious discoveries.</p>

